<augment_code_snippet path="index.html" mode="EDIT">
```html
<!doctype html>
<html class="no-js" lang="">

<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Simple Form with Table</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">
  <meta name="description" content="Simple form with table example">
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Form with Table Example</h1>

    <form id="dataForm">
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="textbox1">First Text:</label>
        <input type="text" id="textbox1" name="textbox1">
      </div>

      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="textbox2">Second Text:</label>
        <input type="text" id="textbox2" name="textbox2">
      </div>

      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="numberSelect">Select Number:</label>
        <input type="number" id="numberSelect" name="numberSelect" min="0" max="100" value="0">
      </div>

      <div class="form-group">
        <input type="button" id="submitBtn" value="Submit" onclick="addToTable()">
      </div>
    </form>

    <table id="dataTable">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>First Text</th>
          <th>Second Text</th>
          <th>Number</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <!-- Table data will be added here -->
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <script>
    function addToTable() {
      const text1 = document.getElementById('textbox1').value;
      const text2 = document.getElementById('textbox2').value;
      const number = document.getElementById('numberSelect').value;

      if (text1 && text2) {
        const tableBody = document.querySelector('#dataTable tbody');
        const newRow = document.createElement('tr');

        newRow.innerHTML = `
          <td>${text1}</td>
          <td>${text2}</td>
          <td>${number}</td>
        `;

        tableBody.appendChild(newRow);

        // Clear form fields
        document.getElementById('textbox1').value = '';
        document.getElementById('textbox2').value = '';
        document.getElementById('numberSelect').value = '0';
      } else {
        alert('Please fill in both text fields');
      }
    }
  </script>
</body>

</html>
```
</augment_code_snippet>

You can also add some CSS to make it look better:

<augment_code_snippet path="css/style.css" mode="EDIT">
```css
/* Add these styles to your existing CSS file */
.container {
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 20px;
}

.form-group {
  margin-bottom: 15px;
}

label {
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 5px;
  font-weight: bold;
}

input[type="text"], input[type="number"] {
  padding: 8px;
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 300px;
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

input[type="button"] {
  padding: 10px 15px;
  background-color: #4CAF50;
  color: white;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

input[type="button"]:hover {
  background-color: #45a049;
}

table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  margin-top: 20px;
}

table, th, td {
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
}

th, td {
  padding: 12px;
  text-align: left;
}

th {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
}

tr:nth-child(even) {
  background-color: #f9f9f9;
}
```
</augment_code_snippet>

This creates a simple form with:
- Two text boxes
- A number input with up/down buttons
- A submit button
- A table that displays the entered data when you click the button

The JavaScript function `addToTable()` collects the form data and adds it as a new row in the table.
