## Changes Made:

Instead of using a simple `rowData.join('\t')` which adds single tabs between all columns, I implemented a custom formatting logic that:

1. **Adds double tabs (`\t\t`)** after the First Text column (index 0)
2. **Adds single tabs (`\t`)** after all other columns except the last one
3. **No tab** after the last column

````javascript path=index.html mode=EXCERPT
// Join with tabs, but add extra tab between First Text (index 0) and Number (index 1)
let formattedRow = '';
rowData.forEach((cellData, index) => {
  if (index === 0) {
    // First Text column - add extra tab after it
    formattedRow += cellData + '\t\t';
  } else if (index === rowData.length - 1) {
    // Last column - no tab after
    formattedRow += cellData;
  } else {
    // Other columns - single tab after
    formattedRow += cellData + '\t';
  }
});
````

