## Changes Made:

Modified the `copyTableToClipboard()` function to use the same selector that the summary table uses for filtering:

<augment_code_snippet path="index.html" mode="EXCERPT">
```javascript
function copyTableToClipboard() {
  const table = document.getElementById('dataTable');
  const rows = table.querySelectorAll('tbody tr:not([style*="display: none"])'); // Only get visible data rows after filtering
```
</augment_code_snippet>

## How it works:

- **Before**: The function copied ALL rows in the table (`tbody tr`)
- **After**: The function now copies only VISIBLE rows (`tbody tr:not([style*="display: none"])`)

This means:

1. **When no filter is applied**: All rows are visible, so all data will be copied (same as before)
2. **When month filter is applied**: Only rows matching the selected month will be copied
3. **When any future filters are added**: Only the visible rows will be copied

The change ensures that when you:
- Filter by a specific month (e.g., "Tháng 5")
- Click the " Copy Table" button
- Only the data from that filtered month will be copied to your clipboard

This is consistent with how the summary table works - it also only processes visible rows after filtering, so now both the summary and copy functions work with the same filtered dataset.
